%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsports-betting-online-gambling-companies-raising-most-money-vc-funding-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epurchase%20lottery%20tickets%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20its%20website%20and%20app.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20the%20jackpot%20for%20both%20Powerball%20and%20Mega%20Millions%20steamrolls%20toward%20six%2C%20seven%2C%20eight-hundred-million%20dollars%2C%20it%20enters%20the%20public%20conscience%20in%20a%20different%20way%2C%20and%20that%20really%20drives%20people%20to%20purchase%20more%20and%20more%20and%20more%2C%26quot%3B%20Khanna%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20right%20%E2%80%94%20the%20reason%20these%20prizes%20keep%20skyrocketing%20is%20because%20people%20like%20you%20and%20me%20keep%20buying%20tickets%20and%20betting%20on%20our%20chances%20to%20win%20big.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20though%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpowerball-odds-why-people-think-theyll-win-2018-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eodds%20of%20winning%20the%20Powerball%3C%2Fa%3E%20jackpot%20are%201%20in%20292%20million%2C%20Americans%20continue%20to%20throw%20their%20money%20at%20the%20game.%20The%20US%20spent%20more%20than%20%24100%20billion%20on%20lottery%20tickets%20and%20games%20in%202021%2C%20according%20to%20the%20North%20American%20Association%20of%20State%20and%20Provincial%20Lotteries.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBehavioral%20experts%20told%20Insider%20in%202019%20that%20humans%20are%20more%20inclined%20to%20bet%20on%20a%20good%20risk%20than%20prepare%20for%20a%20bad%20one%2C%20adding%20that%20it's%20difficult%20to%20conceptualize%20how%20small%20our%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpowerball-odds-why-people-think-theyll-win-2018-10%23at-a-certain-point-we-cant-conceive-of-the-odds-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Echances%20of%20winning%3C%2Fa%3E%20really%20are%2C%20which%20makes%20it%20easier%20for%20us%20to%20throw%20our%20hat%20in%20the%20ring%20regardless%20of%20wha