Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E20%20senators%20are%20warning%20President%20Biden%20against%20a%20defense%20agreement%20with%20Saudi%20Arabia.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIn%20a%20letter%2C%20the%20senators%2C%20all%20Democrats%2C%20say%20such%20an%20agreement%20could%20jeopardize%20US%20interests.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20US%20is%20considering%20a%20defense%20pact%20to%20entice%20Saudi%20Arabia%20to%20normalize%20relations%20with%20Israel.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Biden%20administration%20may%20be%20on%20the%20verge%20of%20damaging%20America's%20reputation%20and%20US%20national%20security%20by%20agreeing%20to%20a%20defense%20pact%20with%20an%20%26quot%3Bauthoritarian%20regime%26quot%3B%20in%20Saudi%20Arabia%2C%20a%20group%20of%2020%20Democratic%20senators%20warned%20in%20a%20letter%20to%20the%20president%20on%20Wednesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20New%20York%20Times%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F09%2F19%2Fus%2Fpolitics%2Fbiden-saudi-defense-treaty.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereported%20last%20month%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20Biden%20administration%20is%20considering%20a%20security%20agreement%20with%20Saudi%20Arabia%20%26quot%3Bresembling%20those%20with%20Japan%20or%20South%20Korea.%26quot%3B%20That%20could%20mean%20US%20forces%20being%20obliged%20to%20defend%20Riyadh%20in%20the%20event%20it%20is%20attacked%2C%20undermining%20Washington's%20stated%20commitment%20to%20democracy%20in%20exchange%20for%20the%20Saudis%20normalizing%20relations%20with%20Israel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20saying%20they%20share%20the%20White%20House's%20goal%20of%20restoring%20ties%20between%20its%20two%20Middle%20Eastern%20allies%2C%20the%20senators%20argue%20that%20a%20defense%20pact%20with%20Saudi%20Arabia%20would%20upend%20decades%20of%20US%20policy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHistorically%2C%20security%20guarantees%20through%20defense%20treaties%20have%20only%20been%20provided%20to%20the%20closest%20of%20US%20allies%3A%20democra