C%20dividing%20the%20chamber%20into%20Democrats%2C%20Republicans%2C%20and%20the%20hard%20right.%20%26quot%3BThose%20are%20the%20three%20that%20exist.%20And%20we're%20the%20plurality.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20sense%2C%20he's%20right.%20In%20January%2C%20House%20Minority%20Leader%20Hakeem%20Jeffries%20won%20more%20votes%20than%20McCarthy%20%E2%80%94%20though%20not%20a%20majority%20%E2%80%94%20the%20first%2011%20times%20the%20House%20voted%20to%20elected%20a%20speaker%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2Finteractive%2F2023%2F01%2F04%2Fus%2Fpolitics%2Fhouse-speaker-vote-tally.html%5C%22%3Eeventually%20falling%20behind%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20McCarthy%20began%20to%20win%20over%20some%20of%20the%20hard-right%20holdouts.%20Democrats%20stayed%20united%20behind%20Jeffries%20the%20whole%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20reality%20was%20enough%20for%20Jeffries%20to%20declare%2C%20in%20a%20statement%20after%20McCarthy's%20ouster%2C%20that%20%26quot%3Btraditional%20Republicans%26quot%3B%20should%20%26quot%3Bjoin%20us%20in%20partnership%20for%20the%20good%20of%20the%20country.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20dust%20settled%20after%20the%20vote%20to%20boot%20McCarthy%20on%20Tuesday%2C%20I%20spotted%20Republican%20Rep.%20Mike%20Lawler%20walking%20away%20from%20the%20Capitol.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELawler%20represents%20a%20New%20York%20district%20that%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20easily%20won%20in%202020%2C%20and%20he's%20postured%20as%20a%20reasonable%20deal-maker%20since%20coming%20to%20Congress.%20Biden%20himself%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Ftherecount%2Fstatus%2F1656363559566077981%5C%22%3Eonce%20described%3C%2Fa%3E%20Lawler%20as%20%26quot%3Bnot%20one%20of%20these%20MAGA%20Republicans%2C%26quot%3B%20much%20to%20the%20horror%20of%20fellow%20Democrats.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20short%2C%20he's%20the%20exact%20type%20of%20Republican%20you%20might%20expect%20to%20cross%20the%20aisle%20in%20a%20%26quot%3Bcoalition%20government%26quot%3B%20de