%20Lok%20Sabha%20Secretariat%20bulletin%20stated.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20the%20second%20time%20that%20the%20Nationalist%20Congress%20Party%20(NCP)%20leader%20has%20been%20disqualified.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOn%20Tuesday%2C%20the%20high%20court%20refused%20to%20suspend%20his%20conviction%20but%20suspended%20the%20sentence.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Fhigh-court%2Fkerala-high-court%2Fkerala-high-court-mp-mohammed-faizal-conviction-disqualification-of-mp-mla-criminal-antecedents-239226%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Justice%20N.%20Nagaresh%20said%20that%20criminalisation%20of%20the%20election%20process%20is%20of%20grave%20concern%20to%20democracy%20and%20if%20persons%20with%20criminal%20antecedents%20are%20permitted%20to%20continue%20as%20elected%20representatives%20even%20after%20conviction%20by%20a%20competent%20court%2C%20%E2%80%9Cthat%20would%20only%20send%20wrong%20signals%20to%20public%20at%20large%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%20data-reader-unique-id%3D%5C%2214%5C%22%3EThe%20judge%20said%20that%20a%20conviction%20can%20only%20be%20suspended%20under%20section%20389%20of%20the%20Code%20of%20Criminal%20Procedure%20(CrPC)%20if%20the%20Court%20was%20satisfied%20that%20the%20case%20was%20frivolous.%20He%20said%20conviction%20can%20be%20suspended%20if%20the%20court%20is%20satisfied%20that%20the%20convicted%20person%20%E2%80%9Cdoes%20not%20suffer%20from%20a%20certain%20disqualification%20or%20damage%20that%20cannot%20be%20undone%E2%80%9D%20only%20in%20rare%20cases%2C%20under%20special%20circumstances.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%20data-reader-unique-id%3D%5C%2214%5C%22%3EThe%20high%20court%20relied%20on%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20recent%20decision%20to%20suspend%20the%20conviction%20of%20Rahul%20Gandhi%2C%20which%20said%20that%20conviction%20%E2%80%9Ccannot%20be%20suspended%20by%20only%20looking%20at%20the%20ramifications%E2%80%9D%20but%20after%20considering%20all%20relevant%20aspects.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20January%20this%20year%2C%20Faizal%20and%20three%20others%20were%20convicted%20for%20attempting%20to%20murder%20a%20Congress%20leader%E2%80%99s%20son-in-law%20during%20the%202009%20general%20elections.%20The%20court%20sentenced%20him%20to%2010%20years%20in%20jail%2C%20which%20led%20to%20his%20automatic%20disqualification%20from%20the%20Lok%20Sabha.%20A%20couple%20of%20weeks%20later%2C%20another%20single-judge%20bench%20of%20the%20Kerala%20high%20court%20suspended%20his%20conviction.%20The%20thrust%20of%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20order%20was%20on%20the%20expenditure%20to%20the%20exchequer%20that%20the%20by-election%20would%20cause.%20He%20was%20eventually%20reinstated%20as%20a%20member%20of%20the%20Lok%20Sabha.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20August%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-court-mohammed-faizal-mp-suspension-set-aside%5C%22%3Eset%20aside%20that%20order%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20asking%20the%20high%20court%20to%20consider%20the%20matter%20afresh.%20It%20said%20that%20if%20the%20high%20court%E2%80%99s%20reasoning%20was%20allowed%20to%20stand%2C%20the%20conviction%20and%20sentence%20of%20every%20elected%20politician%20would%20have%20to%20be%20suspended%20to%20avoid%20the%20financial%20burden%20of%20bye-elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ENote%3A%20This%20article%20was%20originally%20published%20at%206%3A44%20pm%20on%20October%203%2C%202023%20and%20republished%20at%2010%3A05%20pm%20on%20October%204%2C%202023%20after%20Faizal%20was%20disqualified%20as%20an%20MP.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696437313000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2F14133347%2FUntitled-design-13.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fkerala-hc-refuses-stay-conviction-lakshadweep-mp-mohammed-faizal%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20court%20said%20that%20criminalisation%20of%20election%20process%20is%20of%20grave%20concern%20to%20democracy%20and%20if%20persons%20with%20criminal%20antecedents%20are%20permitted%20to%20continue%20as%20elected%20representatives%2C%20that%20would%20only%20send%20wrong%20signals%20to%20public%20at%20large.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fkerala-hc-refuses-stay-conviction-lakshadweep-mp-mohammed-faizal%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Dozens%20of%20cats'%20found%20abandoned%20in%20Abu%20Dhabi%20desert%20as%20authorities%20launch%20investigation%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696437180000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F23%2F10%2F768x432%2Fskynews-cat-abu-dhabi_6309014.jpg%3F20231004173908%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fabu-dhabi-dozens-of-cats-found-abandoned-in-desert-as-authorities-launch-investigation-12976826%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Authorities%20in%20Abu%20Dhabi%20are%20investigating%20reports%20of%20cats%20being%20abandoned%20in%20the%20desert%2C%20with%20dozens%20said%20to%20have%20died.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A110%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fabu-dhabi-dozens-of-cats-found-abandoned-in-desert-as-authorities-launch-investigation-12976826%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fabu-dhabi-dozens-of-cats-found-abandoned-in-desert-as-authorities-launch-investigation-12976826%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fabu-dhabi-dozens-of-cats-found-abandoned-in-desert-as-authorities-launch-investigation-12976826%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Kenyan%20baby%20stealer%20jailed%20for%2025%20years%20after%20BBC%20Africa%20Eye%20expose%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696437052000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2F10DB0%2Fproduction%2F_131004096__mgl7614.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-africa-67010771%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Hospital%20worker%20Fred%20Leparan%20attempted%20to%20sell%20a%20baby%20boy%20to%20an%20undercover%20BBC%20reporter.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A128%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-africa-67010771%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-bbc-co-uk.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-africa-67010771.amp%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-africa-67010771.amp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%26quot%3BSeizures%20On%20Whim...%26quot%3B%3A%20Press%20Bodies%20To%20Chief%20Justice%20After%20NewsClick%20Raids%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EA%20day%20after%20the%20Delhi%20Police%20action%20against%20the%20NewsClick%20portal%2C%20several%20prominent%20press%20organisations%20have%20written%20to%20Chief%20Justice%20Of%20India%20DY%20Chandrachud%2C%20seeking%20evolved%20guidelines%20for%20the%20interrogation%20of%20journalists%20and%20for%20seizures%20from%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIndia's%20freedoms%20will%20be%20safe%20as%20long%20as%20journalists%20can%20speak%20truth%20to%20power%2C%20without%20being%20chilled%20by%20a%20threat%20of%20reprisal%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20press%20bodies%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20press%20bodies%20cited%20the%20instance%20of%20raids%20conducted%20on%20October%203%20on%20the%20homes%20of%2046%20employees%20of%20NewsClick.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20letter%20alleged%20that%20the%20country's%20%26quot%3Binvestigating%20agencies%20have%20been%20misused%20and%20weaponised%20against%20the%20press%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFrame%20norms%20%26quot%3Bto%20discourage%20the%20seizure%20of%20journalists'%20phones%20and%20laptops%20on%20a%20whim%2C%20as%20has%20been%20the%20case%26quot%3B%2C%20read%20the%20letter%20which%20also%20demanded%20to%20ensure%20that%20investigations%20are%20not%20undertaken%20as%20%26quot%3Bfishing%20expeditions%20with%20no%20bearing%20to%20actual%20offences%20and%20finding%20ways%20to%20ensure%20the%20accountability%20of%20state%20agencies%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20journalists%20and%20news%20professionals%2C%20we%20are%20always%20ready%20and%20willing%20to%20cooperate%20with%20any%20bona%20fide%20investigation.%20However%2C%20ad%20hoc%2C%20sweeping%20seizures%20and%20interrogations%20surely%20cannot%20be%20considered%20acceptable%20in%20any%20democratic%20country%2C%20let%20alone%20one%20that%20has%20begun%20advertising%20itself%20as%20the%20'mother%20of%20democracy%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20letter%20has%20been%20signed%20by%2015%20organisations%2C%20including%20the%20Digipub%20News%20India%20Foundation%2C%20Indian%20Women's%20Press%20Corps%2C%20and%20the%20Press%20Club%20of%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20letter%20also%20flagged%20that%20a%20large%20section%20of%20journalists%20in%20India%20are%20%26quot%3Bworking%20under%20the%20threat%20of%20reprisal%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20demanded%20the%20judiciary%20to%20%26quot%3Bconfront%20power%20with%20a%20fundamental%20truth%20-%20that%20there%20is%20a%20Constitution%20to%20which%20we%20are%20all%20answerable%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSubjecting%20journalists%20to%20a%20concentrated%20criminal%20process%20because%20the%20government%20disapproves%20of%20their%20coverage%20of%20national%20and%20international%20affairs%20is%20an%20attempt%20to%20chill%20the%20press%20by%20the%20threat%20of%20reprisal-the%20very%20ingredient%20you%20identified%20as%20a%20threat%20to%20freedom%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20letter%20read.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20do%20not%20say%20that%20journalists%20are%20above%20the%20law.%20We%20are%20not%20and%20do%20not%20wish%20to%20be.%20However%2C%20intimidation%20of%20the%20media%20affects%20the%20democratic%20fabric%20of%20society%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENewsClick%20founder%20Prabir%20Purkayastha%20and%20human%20resources%20head%20Amit%20Chakravarty%2C%20arrested%20in%20a%20case%20filed%20under%20anti-terror%20law%20UAPA%2C%20have%20been%20sent%20to%20police%20custody%20for%20seven%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ECiting%20the%20case%20of%20Siddique%20Kappan%20-%20who%20was%20in%20jail%20for%20more%20than%20two%20years%20before%20securing%20bail%20-%20the%20letter%20demanded%20%26quot%3Ba%20wide%20immunity%20against%20coercion%20must%20be%20read%20into%20the%20constitutional%20provisions%20of%20free%20speech%2C%20and%20methods%20must%20be%20devised%20against%20police%20overreach%20-%20especially%20given%20the%20repeated%20misuse%20of%20these%20powers%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFar%20too%20much%20is%20at%20stake%20to%20test%20every%20case%20at%20the%20end%20of%20a%20trial%20which%20can%20last%20years.%20Journalists%20arrested%20under%20UAPA%20can%20end%20up%20spending%20months%20if%20not%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20ruling%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%20has%20justified%20the%20police%20action%20against%20NewsClick%2C%20saying%20those%20involved%20in%20anti-India%20activities%20will%20face%20the%20strictest%20action%20as%20people%20have%20given%20the%20mandate%20to%20the%20Narendra%20Modi%20government%20to%20deal%20firmly%20with%20such%20elements.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EPolice%20have%20sealed%20NewsClick's%20office%20in%20Delhi.%20Forty-six%20suspects%20were%20questioned%20and%20digital%20devices%2C%20including%20laptops%20and%20mobile%20phones%2C%20besides%20documents%20taken%20away%20for%20examination.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696436880000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-08%2Fbfidjl98_dy-chandrachud_625x300_16_August_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fpress-bodies-to-chief-justice-after-newsclick-raids-seizures-on-whim-4450572%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20day%20after%20the%20Delhi%20Police%20action%20against%20the%20NewsClick%20portal%2C%20several%20prominent%20press%20organisations%20have%20written%