ned%20under%20the%20anti-terror%20law%20Unlawful%20Activities%20(%20Prevention)%20Act%20(UAPA).%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20detention%20of%20several%20people%20working%20for%20%3Cem%3ENewsClick%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0sent%20shockwaves%20across%20countries%20that%20embrace%20democratic%20values%2C%20said%20a%20media%20analyst%20in%20Geneva.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20arrests%20of%20Purkayastha%20and%20Chakravarthy%20came%20on%20the%20evening%20of%20October%203%2C%20after%20early%20morning%20%E2%80%98raids%E2%80%99%20on%20the%20homes%20of%20journalists%2C%20contributors%2C%20columnists%2C%20and%20other%20staff%20of%20the%20%3Cem%3ENewsClick%3C%2Fem%3E.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20seizure%20of%3Cspan%3E%20e%3C%2Fspan%3Electronic%20devices%20%E2%80%93%20laptops%20and%20telephones%20%E2%80%93%20of%20dozens%20of%20journalists%20by%20the%20police%20seemed%20commonplace%20in%20India%20at%20this%20juncture.%20And%20on%20top%20of%20it%2C%20to%20charge%20them%20under%20the%20allegedly%20draconian%20UAPA%2C%20which%20is%20tantamount%20to%20treating%20journalists%20as%20terrorists%2C%20does%20not%20augur%20well%20for%20India%2C%20which%20prides%20itself%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Cmother%20of%20democracy%2C%20the%20analyst%20said.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAgainst%20this%20backdrop%2C%20the%20spokesperson%20in%20the%20office%20of%20the%20Human%20Rights%20Commissioner%20said%3A%20%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20previously%20expressed%20concern%20about%20the%20shrinking%20of%20civic%20space%20in%20India%2C%20in%20particular%20for%20independent%20journalists%20and%20activists%2C%20and%20yesterday%E2%80%99s%20events%20may%20have%20a%20further%20chilling%20effect.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMore%20disturbingly%2C%20those%20who%20are%20being%20targeted%20include%3Cspan%3E%20a%3C%2Fspan%3Euthors%2C%20journalists%2C%20satirists%2C%20historians%20and%20scientists%20associated%20with%C2%A0%3Ci%3ENewsClick.%20%3C%2Fi%3EIn%20all%2C%20more%20than%2040%20persons%20were%20int