k-in%20interview.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EThe%20walk-in%20interview%20will%20be%20held%20on%2007.10.2023%20from%2009%3A30%20AM%20to%2005%3A00%20PM%20at%20the%20Government%20Polytechnic%20College%2C%20Kalamassery%2C%20Ernakulam%20District%2C%20Kerala.%20Latecomers%20are%20not%20allowed%20for%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F323066%2Fchandrayaan-3-the-history-of-how-india-began-one-of-its-most-significant-space-journeys%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einterview.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3C%2Fol%3E%20%3Cp%3EFor%20more%20information%2C%20visit%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.vssc.gov.in%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewebsite.%C2%A0%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EEdited%20by%20Padmashree%20Pande%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696426438000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F%3Fp%3D331506%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Vikram%20Sarabhai%20Space%20Centre%20(VSSC)%20at%20Thiruvananthapuram%20is%20inviting%20applications%20for%20the%20posts%20of%20technician%20apprentices%20and%20graduate%20apprentices.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Sowmya%20Mani%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F331506%2Fisro-vssc-thiruvananthapuram-jobs-apprentice-training-engineers%2F%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Rising%20Food%20Insecurity%20and%20Restrictive%20Agreements%20at%20the%20WTO%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F02%2F07132342%2Ffarmer-unsplash-1200x487-1.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20more%20than%20800%20million%20people%20in%20the%20world%20going%20to%20bed%20hungry%20and%20over%203%20billion%20people%20%E2%80%93%2042%25%20of%20the%20global%20population%20%E2%80%93%20unable%20to%20afford%20a%20healthy%20diet%2C%20food%20insecurity%20has%20reached%20critical%20levels.%20In%20India%2C%2074%25%20of%20the%20population%20is%20unable%20to%20afford%20a%20healthy%20diet%20and%20according%20to%20the%20FAO%2C%20224%20million%20%E2%80%93%2016%25%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20population%20%E2%80%93%20are%20undernourished.%20In%20this%20context%2C%20UNCTAD%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Functad.org%2Fpress-material%2Ftrade-and-development-report-2023%23%3A~%3Atext%3DWorld%2520economic%2520growth%2520is%2520projected%2Cof%2520key%2520markets%2520are%2520needed.%5C%22%3ETrade%20and%20Development%20Report%3C%2Fa%3E%20underscores%20the%20need%20for%20strengthening%20redistributive%20social%20programmes%20to%20defend%20vulnerable%20households%20from%20increased%20food%20prices%20and%20insulate%20farmers%20from%20international%20food%20price%20volatility.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20points%20out%2C%20however%2C%20that%20the%20problem%20cannot%20be%20solved%20purely%20by%20domestic%20efforts%3B%20most%20developing%20countries%2C%20including%20India%2C%20are%20constrained%20by%20insufficient%20policy%20space%20due%20to%20the%20restrictive%20provisions%20of%20some%20Agreements%20at%20the%20WTO%20which%20hinders%20their%20efforts%20to%20develop%20effective%20national%20food%20security%20programmes.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20domestic%20support%20that%20developing%20countries%20can%20give%20to%20their%20farmers%20under%20these%20Agreements%20differs%20widely%20from%20that%20which%20the%20developed%20countries%20can%20provide%2C%20as%20advanced%20countries%20were%20able%20to%20procure%20a%20much%20higher%20binding%20for%20domestic%20support%20to%20their%20farmers%2C%20i.e.%2C%20Aggregate%20Measure%20of%20Support.%20While%20the%20United%20States%20can%20provide%20a%20maximum%20of%20%2419%20billion%2C%20the%20European%20Union%20%2481%20billion%2C%20and%20Japan%20%2436%20billion%2C%20104%20developing%20countries%20can%20provide%20%E2%80%9Czero%E2%80%9D%20support.%20The%20Africa%20Grout%20at%20the%20WTO%20has%20also%20highlighted%20the%20urgent%20need%20to%20revisit%20and%20correct%20this%20inequity.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMore%20importantly%2C%20while%20billions%20of%20dollars%20are%20provided%20as%20subsidies%20to%20the%20farmers%20in%20the%20rich%20countries%2C%20developing%20countries%20like%20India%20are%20unable%20to%20design%20their%20food%20procurement%20programmes%20like%20the%20%E2%80%9Cpublic%20stockholding.%E2%80%9D%20Under%20this%20programme%2C%20governments%20procure%2C%20stock%2C%20and%20distribute%20food%20to%20the%20public.%20In%20most%20cases%20the%20governments%20procure%20food%20at%20a%20minimum%20support%20price%20which%20is%20higher%20than%20the%20market%20price.%20The%20difference%20between%20these%20two%20prices%20is%20considered%20as%20a%20subsidy%20for%20the%20farmers%20under%20the%20WTO%20rules.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EUnder%20the%20%E2%80%9Cde%20minimis%E2%80%9D%20provision%20in%20the%20Agreement%20on%20Agriculture%2C%20a%20ceiling%20is%20set%20for%20procurement%20in%20developing%20countries.%20They%20can%20provide%20this%20support%20with%20respect%20to%20only%2010%25%20of%20the%20value%20of%20production%20of%20both%20product-specific%20and%20non-product%20specific%20support.%20However%2C%20the%20subsidy%20in%20terms%20of%20minimum%20support%20price%20is%20calculated%20using%20the%20reference%20price%20index%20of%201986-1988%20and%20is%20not%20based%20on%20the%20current%20prices%2C%20therefore%20it%20does%20not%20consider%20the%20intervening%20rise%20in%20prices.%20Consequently%2C%20many%20developing%20countries%2C%20including%20India%2C%20have%20breached%20their%20binding%20obligations.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EGiven%20the%20increasing%20volatility%20in%20food%20prices%2C%20at%20the%209th%20Ministerial%20Conference%20in%20Bali%20in%202013%2C%20India%20negotiated%20hard%20on%20this%20issue%2C%20and%20it%20was%20agreed%20that%20there%20is%20a%20need%20to%20update%20the%20rules%20under%20the%20Agreement%20on%20Agriculture%20with%20respect%20to%20public%20stockholding%20of%20food.%20Until%20a%20permanent%20solution%20is%20found%2C%20a%20%E2%80%9Cpeace%20clause%E2%80%9D%20will%20prevail%20which%20implies%20that%20members%20would%20temporarily%20refrain%20from%20lodging%20complaints%20against%20any%20developing%20country%20which%20exceeds%20its%20de-minimis%20limits.%20While%20many%20proposals%20have%20been%20tabled%20with%20respect%20to%20public%20stockholding%20and%20India%20has%20delivered%20many%20statements%20on%20it%2C%20even%20after%20a%20decade%2C%20a%20permanent%20solution%20has%20not%20been%20agreed.%20Given%20the%20rising%20volatility%20in%20international%20prices%20of%20food%20and%20growing%20food%20insecurity%2C%20it%20becomes%20urgent%20to%20provide%20flexibility%20in%20the%20existing%20rules%20and%20a%20permanent%20solution%20to%20this%20issue%20in%20the%20upcoming%20MC13%20in%20February%202014.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EApart%20from%20the%20Aggregate%20Measure%20of%20Support%2C%20advanced%20countries%20are%20also%20able%20to%20provide%20billions%20of%20dollars%20of%20subsidies%20to%20their%20farmers%20under%20the%20%E2%80%9Cgreen%20box%E2%80%9D%20subsidy%2C%20which%20are%20supposed%20to%20be%20non-trade-distorting.%20However%2C%20a%20stream%20of%20independent%20studies%20has%20shown%20that%20green%20box%20subsidies%20shift%20the%20global%20production%20of%20food%20towards%20un-competitive%20producers%20in%20advanced%20countries%2C%20which%20have%20the%20financial%20resources%20to%20provide%20these%20subsidies%2C%20thereby%20adversely%20impacting%20the%20incomes%20of%20farmers%20in%20developing%20countries.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHence%2C%20there%20is%20a%20need%20to%20discipline%20green%20box%20subsidies%20to%20ensure%20more%20equitable%20distribution%20of%20gains%20from%20production%20and%20trade%20in%20food.%20Furthermore%2C%20the%20Report%20argues%20that%20there%20is%20a%20need%20to%20improve%20the%20integration%20of%20small%20farmers%20into%20the%20domestic%20and%20international%20markets%2C%20raising%20their%20bargaining%20power%2C%20and%20making%20the%20gains%20from%20trade%20reach%20the%20poorest%20farmer.%20This%20requires%20addressing%20the%20high%20concentration%20of%20food%20markets%20and%20discouraging%20speculative%20behaviour%20with%20adequate%20regulations.%20Breaking%20the%20food%20monopolies%20and%20revisiting%20WTO%20Agreements%20to%20provide%20policy%20space%20to%20developing%20countries%20becomes%20critical%20for%20progressing%20towards%20global%20food%20security.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ERichard%20Kozul-Wright%2C%20director%2C%20Division%20on%20Globalization%20and%20Development%20Strategies%2C%20UNCTAD.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696426255000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F02%2F07132342%2Ffarmer-unsplash-1200x487-1.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fagriculture%2Frising-food-insecurity-and-restrictive-agreements-at-the-wto%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22There%20is%20a%20need%20to%20improve%20the%20integration%20of%20small%20farmers%20into%20the%20domestic%20and%20international%20markets%2C%20raising%20their%20bargaining%20power%2C%20and%20making%20the%20gains%20from%20trade%20reach%20the%20poorest%20farmer.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fagriculture%2Frising-food-insecurity-and-restrictive-agreements-at-the-wto%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Caine%20Prize%202023%3A%20Senegalese%20married%20couple%20win%20African%20writing%20award%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696426029000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2F17C02%2Fproduction%2F_131328279_image001.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-africa-67005476%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Mame%20Di