%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20National%20Platform%20for%20the%20Rights%20of%20the%20Disabled%20(NPRD)%20has%20released%20a%20statement%20strongly%20condemning%20the%20Delhi%20Police%E2%80%99s%20attack%20on%20the%20independent%20media%20outlet%20%3Cem%3ENewsClick%2C%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3Ehighlighting%20the%20fact%20that%20one%20of%20those%20arrested%20is%20a%C2%A0polio%20survivor%20and%20person%20with%20disability%2C%20who%20uses%20crutches.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20two%20detained%20%E2%80%93%20after%2046%20persons%20linked%20to%20%3Cem%3ENewsclick%3C%2Fem%3E%20were%20subjected%20to%20raids%2C%20device%20seizures%20and%20questionings%20on%20October%203%20%E2%80%93%20and%20remanded%20to%20police%20custody%20is%20Amit%20Chakravarti.%20The%20statement%20notes%20that%20as%20a%20person%20with%20disability%2C%20he%20has%20a%20right%20to%20be%20protected%20from%20inhuman%20treatment%20and%20torture.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EChakravarthi%20is%20an%20administrator%20at%20Newsclick%2C%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Fdelhi-police-conducts-early-morning-raids-at-houses-of-journalists-satirists%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20statement%2C%20signed%20by%20general%20secretary%20Muralidharan%2C%20also%20says%20that%20the%20portal%20has%20been%C2%A0consistently%20championing%20the%20cause%20of%20the%20marginalised%20sections%2C%20including%20disabled%20people.%20%E2%80%9CIn%20this%20people-centric%20approach%2C%20the%20portal%20has%20been%20consistently%20carrying%20reports%20and%20articles%20on%20various%20struggles%20and%20issues%20of%20the%20disabled%20community%20and%20sought%20to%20lend%20a%20voice%20to%20their%20issues%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20reminds%20of%20the%20UN%20conventions%20on%20the%20rights%20of%20persons%20with%20disabilities%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EArticle%2025%20of%20the%20United%20Nations%20Convention%20on%20Rights%20of%20Persons%20with%20Disabilities%20(UNCRPD)%20affirms%20that%20the%20State%20shall%20%E2%80%9CPrevent%20discriminatory%20denial%20of%20health%20care%20or%20health%20services%20or%20food%20and%20fluids%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20disability.%E2%80%9D%20The%20Rights%20of%20Persons%20with%20Disabilities%20Act%2C%202016%20under%20Section%206%20provides%20for%20%E2%80%9CProtection%20from%20cruelty%20and%20inhuman%20treatment%E2%80%9D.%20In%20addition%20to%20the%20legislation%20and%20convention%20on%20disability%20the%20right%20to%20protection%20from%20torture%2C%20cruel%2C%20inhuman%20and%20degrading%20treatment%20and%20the%20right%20to%20be%20treated%20with%20humanity%20and%20respect%20for%20inherent%20dignity%20for%20those%20lawfully%20deprived%20of%20their%20liberty%20is%20specified%20under%20Articles%207%20%26amp%3B%2010%20of%20International%20Covenant%20on%20Civil%20and%20Political%20Rights%20(ICCPR).%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20NPRD%20has%20asked%20that%20all%20reasonable%20accommodations%20should%20be%20provided%20to%20Amit%20Chakravarti%20while%20he%20is%20in%20custody.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CUntil%20his%20release%20he%20should%20be%20lodged%20in%20a%20facilities%20that%20takes%20care%20of%20his%20accessibility%20needs.%20His%20other%20needs%20as%20a%20disabled%20person%20should%20be%20complied%20with%2C%20including%20but%20not%20restricted%20to%20health%20concerns%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20notes.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696423246000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F02%2F10154711%2FUntitled-design-2021-02-10T154651.122.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Fnational-platform-for-the-rights-of-the-disabled-newsclick-amit-chakravarti%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20statement%20National%20Platform%20for%20the%20Rights%20of%20the%20Disabled%20also%20says%20that%20the%20portal%20has%20been%C2%A0consistently%20championing%20the%20cause%20of%20the%20marginalised%20sections%2C%20including%20disabled%20people.%22